exam.examName: Staff Selection Commission Combined Graduate Level
exam.description: SSC CGL (Combined Graduate Level) is considered to be one of the biggest examinations to be conducted for graduate students in India. SSC conducts SSC CGL every year to recruit staff for various posts in the various Ministries and Departments of the Government of India and in its Subordinate Offices. SSC CGL 2021 will be a great opportunity for students looking forward to a position in the reputed organizations under the central government

topic_details.topicName: Sampling distribution of x properties of estimators
Testing of hypothesis for large samples as well as small samples including
Components of variation and their estimation
Laws and Interaction of Demand and Supply
Theory of Factor Pricing(Rent/Wage/Interest and Profit)
Theory of Employment (Classical and Neo-classical Approach)
Fluctuations in the value of Money
Determination of the rate of Exchange
Scope and importance of Public Finance
Collection of data and editing of data
Structural changes in the Indian Economy as seen in National Income Data
Rural Development Co-operation and Panchayati Raj
Five Year Plans and Role of National Development Council
De Moivere’s Theorem and its simple applications
Relation between roots and coefficients of a polynomial equation
Evaluation of symmetric function of roots of cubic
Multiplication of determinants of orders two and three
Rank of a matrix and application of matrices to the solution of linear equations ( in three unknowns )
Tests of convergence of series with positive terms
Solution of Second and higher order linear differential equations with constant coefficients and simple applications
Maclaurins and Taylor’s series ( without proof) and their applications
Maxima and Minima of functions of one and two variables
Quadrature - rectification - volumes and surface area of solids of revolution
Large Sample tests for mean and proportion
Tests of significance based on t- F and Chi-square distributions
Business entrepreneurship (including location - choice of form of business and growth strategies )
Business operations including finance - production - marketing and human resource development
Price-determination under perfect competition and monopoly
Issues involved in planning for economic development
Sectoral analysis of Indian economy including agriculture
Analysis of Univariate data involving measurement of Central tendency and dispersion
Shares and share capital and matters relating to issue and transfers of shares
